The paper focuses on the analysis of malicious mobile applications, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The approach proposed in the paper involves recording and reproducing user interface interactions, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of crowdsourcing for collecting new stimulation traces also relates to social and information networks (cs.SI) and cybersecurity (cs.CY).
